// jul19f ryouko fuzz divergence_000001 (pre-existing: reproduces back
// through jul19c, NOT a taint-gate or review-arc regression).
//
//   interp: window fires the empty window []   jit: silence
//
// The whole call fuses (array::window is EFFECT=Sync — CachedArgs<
// WindowEv>), the val arg (1/0) taints in-kernel, and the DynCall's
// interior-bottom-v2 gate is ALL-OR-NOTHING: any tainted arg skips
// the callee and produces a tainted placeholder. The node-walk's
// seam is PER-SLOT: a bottomed arg is SILENCE (the CachedVals slot
// stays None) and eval still runs when another arg fired — eval
// DECIDES whether it can produce over the partial set. WindowEv's
// eval is total over a missing val when #n:0 (the window needs zero
// elements), so the interp legitimately emits [].
//
// NEEDS RULING: (a) per-slot absence at the DynCall seam — marshal
// the per-arg taint bits through and deliver tainted slots as
// ABSENT, dispatch when any untainted arg fired, let eval decide
// (exact interp parity; the 2026-07-19 ruling's own words — "taint
// the slot, never run eval over poison" — describe this, and the
// whole-call skip over-approximates it); or (b) rule the interp's
// []-on-bottomed-val the bug and require eval to refuse (changes
// canonical window semantics for the degenerate n=0 case).
// Claude leans (a).
array::window(#n: i64:0, [i64:1], i64:1 / i64:0)
